description: Sandals By Salt Water Original  The original Salt-Water sandal is defined by its little-way stitched sole and features a rose gold leather multi strap upper with adjustable ankle strap and buckle fastening.  - Leather upper - Leather sock - Rubber sole - Please note the size on the soles of the shoes is a USA youth size, the size on the box is the correct UK size   About Salt Water  As a way to cope with leather shortages in World War II, Walter Hoy started making his sandals using the scrap leather left over from making military boots. Combined with rust-proof metal tongue buckles and produced in a wide choice of colours and designs, the enduring quality and proven heritage of their sandals is unquestionable. Salt-Water originals are defined by their tough little-way stitched rubber sole, the leather is coated with a water resistant sealant and they mould to the user’s feet with repeated wear.
product_name: Salt Water Original ROSE GOLD LEATHER

The distinctive crepe sole and clean, simple lines enable this heritage design to be instantly recognisable.  - Premium leather upper  - Leather lining  - Crepe sole  - Minimal lace up front     About Clarks Originals  C. & J. Clark International Ltd, trading as Clarks, is a British, international shoe manufacturer and retailer. Founded in 1825 by brothers Cyrus and James Clark in Street, Somerset, the iconic brand is sold worldwide and continues to prosper. Starting as the inventors of slippers, to designing the classic desert boot, to being a hit with hip hop stars with the wallabee, this multi-million pound empire has a history as rich as its assets.
